  "prompt": "What are the legal ramifications of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with significant legal consequences. Potential penalties typically include:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal and/or state prosecution\n- Potential felony charges\n- Prison sentences (often 5-20 years)\n- Substantial monetary fines\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Forfeiture of illegally obtained funds\n- Large financial penalties\n- Restitution payments\n\n3. Professional Consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Career disqualification\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n- Professional reputation damage\n\n4. Civil Consequences\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n- Additional financial judgments\n- Personal and business reputation damage\n\n5. International Implications\n- Potential international legal proceedings\n- Travel restrictions\n- Sanctions\n\nSpecific consequences depend on jurisdiction, amount involved, and specific circumstances of the offense.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these aspects?",
